248
00:12:14.335 --> 00:12:16.403
Evidence transfer requests.
Some of my best work.

249
00:12:18.405 --> 00:12:20.508
Just a couple of hours in
the Gotham Academy Art Lab.

250
00:12:20.542 --> 00:12:22.510
Let me see.

251
00:12:22.544 --> 00:12:24.778
Oh. Looks like
the real deal to me.

252
00:12:24.812 --> 00:12:26.648
Your mug shot is
plastered all over the city.

253
00:12:26.681 --> 00:12:28.315
How are you not
gonna be recognized?

254
00:12:28.349 --> 00:12:30.050
I could help with that.

255
00:12:30.084 --> 00:12:31.653
Look. they only know me
as a scared kid.

256
00:12:31.686 --> 00:12:32.820
They're not expecting
a rookie cop.

257
00:12:32.853 --> 00:12:34.788
Yeah. Exactly.
Which you aren't.

258
00:12:34.822 --> 00:12:36.423
This is too dangerous.

259
00:12:36.457 --> 00:12:38.058
Yeah.
Yeah. it is.

260
00:12:38.092 --> 00:12:41.829
And you know what?
He can handle it.

261
00:12:41.862 --> 00:12:43.698
The Talon would have
turned me into a patty melt

262
00:12:43.732 --> 00:12:45.132
if he hadn't pulled me
out of that car.

263
00:12:45.165 --> 00:12:46.800
And. aah. your problem
is that you are

264
00:12:46.834 --> 00:12:48.670
so busy trying
to protect your brother

265
00:12:48.703 --> 00:12:50.739
that you haven't noticed
that he doesn't need it.

266
00:12:50.771 --> 00:12:52.607
So. maybe it's time
for you to recognize

267
00:12:52.641 --> 00:12:54.074
that he's a total badass.

268
00:12:58.779 --> 00:13:00.848
Toodles.

269
00:13:00.881 --> 00:13:03.350
Thanks for
sticking up for me.

270
00:13:03.384 --> 00:13:04.586
It's nice to have
someone believe in me

271
00:13:04.619 --> 00:13:06.554
even if it is you.

272
00:13:06.588 --> 00:13:09.156
Oh. yeah. I just
said that because

273
00:13:09.189 --> 00:13:12.226
there's something I need
you to do for me.

274
00:13:42.423 --> 00:13:43.991
Mr. March. can we get
a picture over here?

275
00:13:45.959 --> 00:13:47.361
Mr. and Mrs. March.

276
00:13:47.394 --> 00:13:48.862
Please. call me Rebecca.

277
00:13:48.896 --> 00:13:50.230
It's nice to finally meet you.

278
00:13:51.465 --> 00:13:53.735
It's a shame we won't
be seeing your parents.

279
00:13:53.768 --> 00:13:56.805
Your mom's been MIA from
the club for weeks now.

280
00:13:56.837 --> 00:13:59.006
Yeah. Dad's taping
"Quiz Bowl" tonight.

281
00:13:59.039 --> 00:14:01.543
Mom's been spending more time
at the studio to support him.

282
00:14:01.576 --> 00:14:04.178
Of course.
Well. they must be
so proud.

283
00:14:04.211 --> 00:14:06.880
Brody told us you're on
the fast track for MIT.

284
00:14:06.914 --> 00:14:08.750
following in
your dad's footsteps.

285
00:14:08.783 --> 00:14:10.951
Same as Brody
now going to State.

286
00:14:10.984 --> 00:14:13.887
Heard you were
quite the fencer
in your day. Mr. March.

287
00:14:13.921 --> 00:14:15.557
Won State 4 years running.

288
00:14:15.590 --> 00:14:16.857
Shall we?

289
00:14:19.393 --> 00:14:20.662
No pressure.

290
00:14:20.695 --> 00:14:22.296
You'll do fine.
I'm certain.

291
00:14:22.329 --> 00:14:24.498
Though I doubt we can
count on your next opponent

292
00:14:24.532 --> 00:14:27.635
also being arrested for
murdering his own father.

293
00:14:27.669 --> 00:14:29.069
Hey. How you doing?

294
00:15:08.976 --> 00:15:10.978
Hi there.

295
00:15:13.914 --> 00:15:15.750
Turner.
what are you doing here?

296
00:15:15.784 --> 00:15:18.686
Waiting on a "thank you"
for stopping him
from shooting you?

297
00:15:18.720 --> 00:15:20.988
One. I had him.
Two. now I can't

298
00:15:21.021 --> 00:15:23.858
question him to find out
what they were
planning next.

299
00:15:23.892 --> 00:15:25.125
So. thank you.

300
00:15:26.193 --> 00:15:27.829
How'd you even
find this place?

301
00:15:27.862 --> 00:15:29.631
The rocket that
took down that airship

302
00:15:29.664 --> 00:15:32.266
came from the north. so.
from the point of impact.

303
00:15:32.299 --> 00:15:34.001
it's a straight line
to this area.

304
00:15:34.034 --> 00:15:36.771
There are. like.
50 warehouses in this area.

305
00:15:36.805 --> 00:15:38.472
How did you narrow it down
to this one?

306
00:15:39.541 --> 00:15:42.242
When I was little.
my dad and I
used to play a game.

307
00:15:42.276 --> 00:15:44.111
He called it
"Sore Thumb."

308
00:15:44.144 --> 00:15:46.514
Wherever we were--
dinners. parties--

309
00:15:46.548 --> 00:15:47.782
he would have me
pick out

310
00:15:47.816 --> 00:15:49.416
the thing that
didn't belong.

311
00:15:49.450 --> 00:15:50.852
I always thought
it was just a game

312
00:15:50.885 --> 00:15:52.085
to entertain
a bored kid.

313
00:15:52.119 --> 00:15:53.521
but turns out...

314
00:15:53.555 --> 00:15:55.523
He was teaching you
situational awareness.

315
00:15:55.557 --> 00:15:58.292
Yup. So. when I saw
that this warehouse

316
00:15:58.325 --> 00:16:00.394
was the only one
without security lights

317
00:16:00.427 --> 00:16:02.996
and the gates were
padlocked from the inside.

318
00:16:03.030 --> 00:16:05.533
I suspected somebody was
trying to hide something.

319
00:16:07.434 --> 00:16:10.572
Looks like you put
those skills to good use.

320
00:16:10.605 --> 00:16:12.640
I just can't figure out why
he would teach them to me

321
00:16:12.674 --> 00:16:14.007
if he didn't want me
to use them.

322
00:16:14.943 --> 00:16:16.276
I'm sure he had a reason.

323
00:16:26.386 --> 00:16:28.656
These are from
Ace Chemicals.

324
00:16:28.690 --> 00:16:30.625
So. it wasn't
a terrorist attack.

325
00:16:30.658 --> 00:16:32.459
Crashing that airship
into Ace Chemicals
was to cover the fact

326
00:16:32.493 --> 00:16:34.228
that the Mutants
were robbing the place.

327
00:16:34.261 --> 00:16:36.029
What are they planning to do
with a bunch of chemicals?

328
00:16:42.971 --> 00:16:44.204
They're empty.

329
00:16:46.473 --> 00:16:48.475
Whatever they were planning.
they already did it.

330
00:17:03.892 --> 00:17:05.292
Good to see you. Martin.

331
00:17:09.831 --> 00:17:11.031
Miss Brown.

332
00:17:12.834 --> 00:17:13.868
How are you
this evening?

333
00:17:13.902 --> 00:17:15.068
Ah. Should I
get my lawyer

334
00:17:15.102 --> 00:17:16.504
down here before
I answer that?

335
00:17:17.639 --> 00:17:19.406
Harvey Dent.

336
00:17:19.439 --> 00:17:23.243
Gotham's white knight...
in black tie.

337
00:17:23.277 --> 00:17:25.345
Lincoln. Good to see you.

338
00:17:25.379 --> 00:17:27.749
Have you met
my wife Rebecca?

339
00:17:27.782 --> 00:17:30.685
No. I don't
believe I have.
Pleasure to meet you.

340
00:17:30.718 --> 00:17:33.621
So. if you're here
glad-handing the donor class.

341
00:17:33.655 --> 00:17:35.389
I assume the rumors are true

342
00:17:35.422 --> 00:17:36.891
and you are running for mayor.

343
00:17:36.925 --> 00:17:38.158
Right now.
my focus is on

344
00:17:38.191 --> 00:17:40.260
the current job
I was elected to do.

345
00:17:40.294 --> 00:17:41.896
Is that right?
All right.

346
00:17:41.930 --> 00:17:43.731
Well. if you ever hope to be

347
00:17:43.765 --> 00:17:45.633
a politician in this town.

348
00:17:45.667 --> 00:17:47.635
better learn how to lie
better than that.

349
00:17:51.906 --> 00:17:53.240
I have to disagree
with my husband.

350
00:17:53.273 --> 00:17:55.142
I think you lie
quite well.

351
00:17:57.879 --> 00:18:00.615
I almost believed you when
you told him we'd never met.

352
00:18:13.595 --> 00:18:16.263
Sign 'em out.
you gotta sign 'em back in.

353
00:18:16.296 --> 00:18:18.766
It's called chain of custody.

354
00:18:18.800 --> 00:18:19.834
Yeah.

355
00:18:21.368 --> 00:18:22.402
Ahem.

356
00:18:24.104 --> 00:18:25.372
How you doing?

357
00:18:26.874 --> 00:18:29.010
- What do you want?
- Yeah. I'm from
Somerset Precinct.

358
00:18:29.043 --> 00:18:30.545
I just got a case file
transfer request.

359
00:18:30.578 --> 00:18:32.680
Does this look like
the Records Room to you?

360
00:18:32.714 --> 00:18:34.147
Uh. uh--

361
00:18:34.181 --> 00:18:35.449
Down the hall.
third door on the left.

362
00:18:35.482 --> 00:18:37.785
Look for a sign
that says "Records."

363
00:18:41.055 --> 00:18:42.255
Hey.

364
00:18:45.793 --> 00:18:47.194
Do they not teach you
anything over there

365
00:18:47.227 --> 00:18:48.663
at Somerset. rook?

366
00:18:50.598 --> 00:18:54.602
Coffee. You come into another
man's shop asking for stuff.

367
00:18:54.636 --> 00:18:56.571
a little juice of the bean
goes a long way.

368
00:18:56.604 --> 00:18:58.640
Right. I'll--I'll
remember that. sir.
Thank you.

369
00:18:58.673 --> 00:19:00.875
Yeah. I'll remember you.

370
00:19:10.084 --> 00:19:12.386
Uh. what's all this?

371
00:19:12.419 --> 00:19:14.254
We were kind of hoping
you could tell us.

372
00:19:14.287 --> 00:19:16.124
We found these chemicals
and some kind of blueprints

373
00:19:16.156 --> 00:19:18.258
trashed at a Mutant Gang
stash house.

374
00:19:18.291 --> 00:19:20.360
Any idea what they're up to?

375
00:19:20.394 --> 00:19:22.730
Well. you've got
nitrobromide

376
00:19:22.764 --> 00:19:24.197
and uridium oxidate.

377
00:19:24.231 --> 00:19:25.867
Not much you can make
out of those.

378
00:19:25.900 --> 00:19:28.636
They're both solubles.
They wouldn't even
cause a reaction

379
00:19:28.670 --> 00:19:32.707
unless they were put under
pressure and aerosolized.

380
00:19:36.010 --> 00:19:37.812
Damn. It looks like
they're making

381
00:19:37.845 --> 00:19:39.580
some kind of
poison gas bomb.

382
00:19:39.614 --> 00:19:40.815
To gas the city?

383
00:19:40.848 --> 00:19:42.215
No. If you
release it outdoors.

384
00:19:42.249 --> 00:19:43.618
it'll dissipate
too quickly.

385
00:19:43.651 --> 00:19:45.252
For it to work. it needs
to stay concentrated.

386
00:19:45.285 --> 00:19:46.821
like in an enclosed area.

387
00:19:46.854 --> 00:19:48.488
- The GCPD.
- No.

388
00:19:48.523 --> 00:19:51.092
Now that the cops
have Vernon in a cage.

389
00:19:51.125 --> 00:19:52.292
I don't think
the Mutant Gang
would risk

390
00:19:52.325 --> 00:19:53.695
killing their leader.

391
00:19:53.728 --> 00:19:55.462
I know what
my daddy would do.

392
00:19:59.399 --> 00:20:00.735
He would make a statement.

393
00:20:03.604 --> 00:20:07.307
All right.
What does poison gas do?

394
00:20:07.340 --> 00:20:08.843
Uh. it kills people?

395
00:20:08.876 --> 00:20:10.545
Well. yes. but how?

396
00:20:10.578 --> 00:20:12.312
- It chokes you to death.
- Ding ding ding!

397
00:20:12.345 --> 00:20:14.549
Yes. And who better
to choke with it

398
00:20:14.582 --> 00:20:16.851
than the people who've
had Gotham by the throat

399
00:20:16.884 --> 00:20:18.152
since the very beginning?

400
00:20:18.186 --> 00:20:20.253
The ones who are.
as we speak.

401
00:20:20.287 --> 00:20:22.924
congratulating themselves
between bites of

402
00:20:22.957 --> 00:20:24.391
little. overpriced
fish eggs.

403
00:20:24.424 --> 00:20:25.392
The Founders Gala.

404
00:20:25.425 --> 00:20:26.393
Yes! You are on fire

405
00:20:26.426 --> 00:20:27.762
today. Little Bird.

406
00:20:27.795 --> 00:20:28.863
I mean. come on.
All those

407
00:20:28.896 --> 00:20:29.997
well-heeled hypocrites.

408
00:20:30.031 --> 00:20:32.432
just gasping
for rarefied air.

409
00:20:32.466 --> 00:20:34.736
The mayor.
The district attorney.

410
00:20:34.769 --> 00:20:35.803
Stephanie.

411
00:20:42.342 --> 00:20:43.911
Two virgin mojitos.

412
00:20:47.515 --> 00:20:49.951
Really? 'Cause this one
tastes pretty slutty to me.

413
00:20:49.984 --> 00:20:52.720
Yeah. I tipped
the bartender a 20
to pretend I'm 21.

414
00:20:52.754 --> 00:20:54.454
You know. given our
recent brushes with the law.

415
00:20:54.488 --> 00:20:56.023
I'm not sure adding
underage drinking

416
00:20:56.057 --> 00:20:57.558
to our rap sheets
is a good idea.

417
00:20:57.592 --> 00:20:59.359
You're about to have dinner
with my parents.

418
00:20:59.392 --> 00:21:01.662
Trust me. you are
going to need it.

419
00:21:05.700 --> 00:21:06.667
Your mom seems nice.

420
00:21:08.335 --> 00:21:09.670
And my dad?

421
00:21:11.739 --> 00:21:12.907
Your mom seems nice.

422
00:21:12.940 --> 00:21:15.943
Huh. Yeah.
She is.

423
00:21:19.747 --> 00:21:22.449
It's not always easy being
married to Lincoln March.

424
00:21:22.482 --> 00:21:24.719
even though she
makes it seem that way.

425
00:21:24.752 --> 00:21:27.287
Starting to get the sense
it's not easy being his son.

426
00:21:34.629 --> 00:21:36.531
I have to get this.
Sorry.

427
00:21:36.564 --> 00:21:37.565
Yeah.

428
00:21:39.934 --> 00:21:43.137
Yes. the party is awful.
the lava cake is garbage.

429
00:21:43.171 --> 00:21:44.872
my feet are killing me.
and I'm having a terrible time.

430
00:21:44.906 --> 00:21:47.208
Steph. listen.
You have to get out of there.

431
00:21:47.241 --> 00:21:48.375
What? Why?

432
00:21:48.408 --> 00:21:49.744
The Mutant Gang's
about to do

433
00:21:49.777 --> 00:21:50.978
something terrible.

434
00:21:54.381 --> 00:21:56.083
- Who was that?
- Shots fired.

435
00:21:59.187 --> 00:22:01.222
Grenade!

436
00:22:18.773 --> 00:22:20.942
No need to panic.

437
00:22:20.975 --> 00:22:24.344
We're just here to provide
the evening's entertainment.

438
00:22:25.313 --> 00:22:27.248
Do you all like games?

439
00:22:27.281 --> 00:22:30.785
Because I have one
that I think you'll love.

440
00:22:32.887 --> 00:22:34.755
It's a very simple game.

441
00:22:34.789 --> 00:22:36.023
It's called...

442
00:22:37.424 --> 00:22:39.359
"What Does This Button Do?"

443
00:22:41.696 --> 00:22:44.332
It's a chaotic
scene here at City Hall

444
00:22:44.364 --> 00:22:46.868
as the Founders Gala
has been taken hostage

445
00:22:46.901 --> 00:22:49.670
by the Mutant Gang. who have
barricaded themselves inside.

446
00:22:49.704 --> 00:22:53.274
threatening to detonate
a chemical explosive

447
00:22:53.307 --> 00:22:55.543
if the GCPD does not
release their leader.

448
00:22:55.576 --> 00:22:58.279
Vernon Wagner.
by 10 p.m. tonight.

449
00:22:58.312 --> 00:23:01.414
In these dark times.
I'm sure I'm not alone

450
00:23:01.448 --> 00:23:04.886
in feeling that Gotham
could use a Batman.

451
00:23:04.919 --> 00:23:08.556
Isn't that the truth?
In other news. Gotham...

452
00:23:13.261 --> 00:23:15.363
So. you guys
are...going in?

453
00:23:15.395 --> 00:23:16.731
We were kind of hoping
you would join us.

454
00:23:16.764 --> 00:23:18.232
Uh. why the hell
would I do that?

455
00:23:18.266 --> 00:23:19.499
You know how
to disable a bomb.

456
00:23:19.533 --> 00:23:21.569
Yeah. Step One:
call the bomb squad.

457
00:23:21.602 --> 00:23:24.739
They don't have
the instruction manual.
We do.

458
00:23:24.772 --> 00:23:26.641
Besides. if they go in
and kick the door down.

459
00:23:26.674 --> 00:23:28.342
then the Mutants will
just set off the bomb.

460
00:23:28.376 --> 00:23:30.511
Sorry. how is what you're
planning any different?

461
00:23:30.544 --> 00:23:33.114
Well. you don't
have to go through
the front door.

462
00:23:33.147 --> 00:23:36.183
Decommissioned subway tunnels
will take you right under it.

463
00:23:36.217 --> 00:23:37.852
Then you could
pop up into City Hall

464
00:23:37.885 --> 00:23:39.921
like a stripper
popping out of a cake.

465
00:23:39.954 --> 00:23:42.455
But you would need
someone to open the door
from the inside.

466
00:23:42.489 --> 00:23:44.992
If I could arrange that.
would you show us the way?

467
00:23:45.026 --> 00:23:47.328
Why would I risk
my life to save
a bunch of people

468
00:23:47.361 --> 00:23:48.629
who don't give
a damn about me?

469
00:23:48.663 --> 00:23:50.264
Same reason we saved you
from the Talon.

470
00:23:50.298 --> 00:23:51.498
You do realize
it's impossible

471
00:23:51.532 --> 00:23:53.034
to guilt me into
anything. right?

472
00:23:54.535 --> 00:23:56.737
Fine. You'll get to punch
a bunch of Mutants.

473
00:23:56.771 --> 00:23:59.206
Oh! Should've led
with that.

474
00:23:59.240 --> 00:24:00.574
I'll get my purse.

475
00:24:03.044 --> 00:24:05.880
All officers.
report to the briefing room.

476
00:24:09.383 --> 00:24:11.252
You.

477
00:24:11.285 --> 00:24:12.920
Briefing. Now.

478
00:24:12.954 --> 00:24:15.022
I really gotta get
these records down
to Somerset. though.

479
00:24:15.056 --> 00:24:16.290
All hands on deck. rook.

480
00:24:16.324 --> 00:24:18.491
Hostage situation
at City Hall.

481
00:24:18.526 --> 00:24:20.061
Briefing room. Now.

482
00:24:28.169 --> 00:24:30.304
Take a seat.

483
00:24:30.338 --> 00:24:32.373
All right now.
All right. everybody.

484
00:24:32.406 --> 00:24:34.241
Listen up.
Settle down.

485
00:24:34.275 --> 00:24:35.643
We got a hostage situation.

486
00:24:56.964 --> 00:24:58.966
Here you thought you wouldn't
make this year's Gala.

487
00:24:59.000 --> 00:25:01.335
Not exactly how I wanted
to join the party.

488
00:25:01.369 --> 00:25:02.670
Everyone. stay on comms.

489
00:25:02.703 --> 00:25:04.005
I'll do a sweep
while you guys

490
00:25:04.038 --> 00:25:05.706
figure out where
they put the bomb.

491
00:25:05.740 --> 00:25:07.008
For maximum dispersal.
they'll have put it

492
00:25:07.041 --> 00:25:08.075
in the HVAC system.

493
00:25:08.109 --> 00:25:09.543
Boiler room's this way.

494
00:25:09.577 --> 00:25:10.611
But there might be
some of those Mutants

495
00:25:10.644 --> 00:25:11.912
between here and there.

496
00:25:18.319 --> 00:25:19.553
- Yah!
- Uhh!

497
00:25:21.455 --> 00:25:23.991
Hmm.

498
00:25:25.593 --> 00:25:27.328
We gotta get this thing
out of here.

499
00:25:27.361 --> 00:25:29.196
Wait. wait.

500
00:25:29.230 --> 00:25:30.464
See that?

501
00:25:30.498 --> 00:25:32.233
It's a mercury
tilt switch.

502
00:25:32.266 --> 00:25:33.868
Used to use it
in old thermostats.

503
00:25:33.901 --> 00:25:35.703
You move it.
mercury closes the circuit.

504
00:25:35.736 --> 00:25:37.171
Uh. what
does that mean?

505
00:25:37.204 --> 00:25:38.305
It means the Mutants

506
00:25:38.339 --> 00:25:39.373
are smarter than we thought.

507
00:25:39.407 --> 00:25:42.443
You move
this thing--boom.

508
00:25:42.476 --> 00:25:44.011
Then we have to
disable it here.

509
00:25:50.017 --> 00:25:53.054
All right. listen up.
Rings. watches.

510
00:25:53.087 --> 00:25:55.990
Trinkets. All in the bag.

511
00:25:56.023 --> 00:25:58.993
Make a donation. everybody.
Let's go.

512
00:25:59.026 --> 00:26:00.628
- I'll take that.
- Brody.

513
00:26:00.661 --> 00:26:02.696
- Uhh!
- Come on. come on.

514
00:26:09.370 --> 00:26:12.006
There's
a lot of red tape and I don't
have that kind of authority.

515
00:26:12.039 --> 00:26:14.075
I don't care how much
red tape you've
gotta cut through.

516
00:26:14.108 --> 00:26:15.943
There's gonna be
a lot more red down here

517
00:26:15.976 --> 00:26:16.811
if you don't!

518
00:26:16.844 --> 00:26:19.514
Release him.
On my order.

519
00:26:19.548 --> 00:26:22.517
Huh. You hear that?

520
00:26:22.551 --> 00:26:24.051
So. here's what
you're gonna do.

521
00:26:28.789 --> 00:26:30.891
Do I honestly have to
tell you what will happen

522
00:26:30.925 --> 00:26:32.827
if you give in
to their demands?

523
00:26:32.860 --> 00:26:35.029
Um. we make it
out of this alive?

524
00:26:35.062 --> 00:26:38.632
You will be sending
a message to every criminal

525
00:26:38.666 --> 00:26:41.035
that not only do we
negotiate with terrorists.

526
00:26:41.068 --> 00:26:42.703
but we give them
everything they want.

527
00:26:42.736 --> 00:26:44.672
Hardly. We're trading
one Mutant Leader

528
00:26:44.705 --> 00:26:46.240
for the rest of his gang.

529
00:26:46.273 --> 00:26:47.542
This place is surrounded.

530
00:26:47.576 --> 00:26:49.210
They're not
getting outta here.

531
00:26:49.243 --> 00:26:52.413
And I am sending a message
to the criminals. Harvey.

532
00:26:52.446 --> 00:26:54.014
Don't mess with us.

533
00:27:01.956 --> 00:27:03.691
Careful. Don't want
to get bomb

534
00:27:03.724 --> 00:27:05.159
all over your Valentino.

535
00:27:05.192 --> 00:27:06.393
It's a May Nickel.

536
00:27:06.427 --> 00:27:08.662
And that is
a mutating algorithm

537
00:27:08.696 --> 00:27:10.664
that deletes itself
once complete.

538
00:27:10.698 --> 00:27:13.400
Uh. what happens
when it deletes itself?

539
00:27:13.434 --> 00:27:14.536
It deletes us.

540
00:27:17.104 --> 00:27:18.439
Don't want this one
getting loose

541
00:27:18.472 --> 00:27:20.074
while I go handle his buddies.

542
00:27:20.107 --> 00:27:22.943
Uh. guys?
I just searched
for the frequency

543
00:27:22.977 --> 00:27:24.311
that'll deactivate this thing

544
00:27:24.345 --> 00:27:26.447
and there isn't one.

545
00:27:26.480 --> 00:27:28.082
Just one to activate it.

546
00:27:28.115 --> 00:27:29.850
So. it was meant to turn on
and never turn off.

547
00:27:29.884 --> 00:27:31.819
So. the bomb's going off
no matter what?

548
00:27:31.852 --> 00:27:33.821
That'd kill the Mutants
along with us.

549
00:27:34.989 --> 00:27:36.657
Unless they
planned ahead.

550
00:27:37.758 --> 00:27:39.193
They all brought these.

551
00:27:40.161 --> 00:27:41.962
Maybe they always intended
to gas the place.

552
00:27:41.996 --> 00:27:44.498
Gotta say. it's kind of
the perfect escape plan.

553
00:27:44.533 --> 00:27:47.368
The GCPD releases the Mutant
Leader. they set off the bomb.

554
00:27:47.401 --> 00:27:50.738
The GCPD doesn't release
the Mutant Leader.
they set off the bomb.

555
00:27:50.771 --> 00:27:52.106
and then they all
peace out of here while

556
00:27:52.139 --> 00:27:54.175
seizures and suffocation
get to fight

557
00:27:54.208 --> 00:27:55.644
over what kills us first.

558
00:27:55.676 --> 00:27:57.512
Great. Huh.
Just gonna hang on to this.

559
00:27:57.546 --> 00:27:59.013
How much time do we
have to defuse it?

560
00:27:59.046 --> 00:28:00.314
42 minutes.
And that's if

561
00:28:00.347 --> 00:28:01.448
the GCPD doesn't release

562
00:28:01.482 --> 00:28:02.517
the Mutant Leader before then.

563
00:28:02.551 --> 00:28:03.851
We have to warn them not to.

564
00:28:03.884 --> 00:28:05.252
Buy ourselves as much
time as possible.

565
00:28:05.286 --> 00:28:06.720
Yeah. We're the last ones
they'll believe.

566
00:28:07.855 --> 00:28:12.092
There is one person
the GCPD will believe. Harvey.

567
00:28:13.528 --> 00:28:15.863
I just gotta make him
believe me first.

568
00:28:15.896 --> 00:28:18.132
OK. and if he doesn't.
he'll have you arrested.

569
00:28:20.367 --> 00:28:21.702
You're gonna risk that?

570
00:28:23.638 --> 00:28:25.372
A lot of people
will die if I don't.

571
00:28:29.511 --> 00:28:30.778
Sit down now. Quiet.

572
00:28:30.811 --> 00:28:32.880
Nobody's gonna get hurt.

573
00:28:32.913 --> 00:28:34.315
Calm down.

574
00:28:34.348 --> 00:28:36.685
We've already taken
what we wanted from you.

575
00:28:36.717 --> 00:28:37.985
Have a seat.

576
00:28:39.720 --> 00:28:41.055
Come with me.

577
00:28:41.088 --> 00:28:42.856
Sit down now. Quiet.

578
00:28:44.058 --> 00:28:47.127
Ahh. OK. OK.

579
00:28:48.262 --> 00:28:50.565
If you're gonna kill me.
just get it over with.

580
00:28:50.599 --> 00:28:51.999
I'm not gonna kill you.

581
00:28:54.068 --> 00:28:55.135
Turner.

582
00:28:58.072 --> 00:29:00.274
What the hell
are you doing here?

583
00:29:00.307 --> 00:29:01.475
We don't have much time.

584
00:29:02.977 --> 00:29:04.778
That gas bomb is
in the boiler room.

585
00:29:04.812 --> 00:29:06.280
and as soon as their leader
is released. the Mutant Gang

586
00:29:06.313 --> 00:29:07.381
are gonna set it off.

587
00:29:07.414 --> 00:29:08.816
That's their exit strategy.

588
00:29:08.849 --> 00:29:10.518
Kill everybody here.

589
00:29:10.552 --> 00:29:11.653
escape in the chaos.

590
00:29:11.686 --> 00:29:12.987
You show up here

591
00:29:13.020 --> 00:29:14.522
and you're dressed
like one of them

592
00:29:14.556 --> 00:29:15.789
and now you're
telling me that you know

593
00:29:15.823 --> 00:29:17.659
what they're
planning to do? How?

594
00:29:17.692 --> 00:29:19.393
You need to trust me.

595
00:29:19.426 --> 00:29:20.595
How can I do that?

596
00:29:20.629 --> 00:29:22.930
You're a fugitive
who ran.

597
00:29:22.963 --> 00:29:24.064
Because I was framed.

598
00:29:24.098 --> 00:29:26.668
Then why not
let me help you?

599
00:29:26.701 --> 00:29:28.202
Because you can't.

600
00:29:28.235 --> 00:29:29.870
You asked me before if
I knew what that coin

601
00:29:29.903 --> 00:29:31.573
they found
on my dad meant.

602
00:29:31.606 --> 00:29:33.207
I didn't know then.

603
00:29:33.240 --> 00:29:35.209
But I do now.

604
00:29:35.242 --> 00:29:37.679
It's the symbol of
the Court of Owls.

605
00:29:37.712 --> 00:29:39.980
They're a secret cabal
that's been
pulling strings in Gotham

606
00:29:40.014 --> 00:29:41.683
since the city was founded.

607
00:29:41.716 --> 00:29:42.983
Turner. this is insane.

608
00:29:43.017 --> 00:29:46.320
Listen. The Court
killed my dad.

609
00:29:48.088 --> 00:29:49.456
And now they're
trying to kill me.

610
00:29:50.592 --> 00:29:51.825
And the others.

611
00:29:52.761 --> 00:29:54.328
We can't trust anyone.

612
00:29:55.597 --> 00:29:56.930
Then why trust me?

613
00:29:58.399 --> 00:29:59.967
Because my dad did.

614
00:30:06.608 --> 00:30:08.075
What do you need me to do?

615
00:30:11.713 --> 00:30:13.715
We could try to cut off
the outflow of the aerosol.

616
00:30:13.748 --> 00:30:15.382
Stop it
from releasing the gas.

617
00:30:15.416 --> 00:30:17.051
And if the stainless steel
can't contain the pressure.

618
00:30:17.084 --> 00:30:18.520
then. congratulations.
you've just turned

619
00:30:18.553 --> 00:30:19.853
a chemical bomb
into a regular bomb.

620
00:30:19.887 --> 00:30:21.756
I suppose you have
a better idea?

621
00:30:21.790 --> 00:30:23.324
Yeah. Not doing your idea.

622
00:30:23.357 --> 00:30:24.992
Right. because
Gotham Academy is renowned

623
00:30:25.025 --> 00:30:26.728
for its Honors
Bomb Defusing classes.

624
00:30:26.761 --> 00:30:29.263
Nope. just
basic science.

625
00:30:29.296 --> 00:30:31.065
We're better off
disrupting the power source

626
00:30:31.098 --> 00:30:33.000
to the valve
that pressurizes it.

627
00:30:33.033 --> 00:30:35.336
That's your solution?
Cut the wire?

628
00:30:35.369 --> 00:30:37.271
What's next?
Bang on it with a hammer?

629
00:30:37.304 --> 00:30:39.006
The Mutants could've
built in a hidden redundancy.

630
00:30:39.039 --> 00:30:40.575
in which case
you cut the primary.

631
00:30:40.608 --> 00:30:43.243
this thing hot-boxes
half the city's
power players.

632
00:30:43.277 --> 00:30:44.912
Oh. uh. and us.

633
00:30:44.945 --> 00:30:46.614
Can you read me?

634
00:30:46.648 --> 00:30:48.817
Me and Duela took out
as many Mutants as we could.

635
00:30:48.849 --> 00:30:51.051
All that's left are
the ones in the Gallery.

636
00:30:51.085 --> 00:30:52.853
How are you two
doing down there?

637
00:30:55.690 --> 00:30:56.924
Can I talk to you?

638
00:30:56.957 --> 00:30:58.192
You have
to recall the order

639
00:30:58.225 --> 00:30:59.527
to release
the Mutant Leader.

640
00:30:59.561 --> 00:31:00.829
Why the hell
would I do that?

641
00:31:00.861 --> 00:31:02.296
Because if you don't.
we're all dead.

642
00:31:02.329 --> 00:31:03.832
It's a double-cross.
They're gonna gas this place

643
00:31:03.864 --> 00:31:05.432
the moment
you set him free.

644
00:31:05.466 --> 00:31:07.368
Who told you that?

645
00:31:07.401 --> 00:31:10.170
I'm asking you to please
just trust me on this.

646
00:31:10.204 --> 00:31:12.039
Trust the guy
that wants my job?

647
00:31:18.212 --> 00:31:19.547
Prisoner coming through.

648
00:31:23.718 --> 00:31:26.286
Delta on point.
Transfer team ready.

649
00:31:29.156 --> 00:31:30.592
Let's move him out now.

650
00:31:36.631 --> 00:31:38.298
And things just got worse.

651
00:31:39.400 --> 00:31:41.235
Cullen says they've
released the Mutant Leader.

652
00:31:43.103 --> 00:31:44.572
Carrie. you guys need
to take out the rest of

653
00:31:44.606 --> 00:31:46.373
those Mutants. like. now.

654
00:31:46.407 --> 00:31:49.343
As you requested.
Vernon Wagner has been

655
00:31:49.376 --> 00:31:51.746
released into
the sewer system.

656
00:31:51.780 --> 00:31:53.313
Well ahead of
your deadline.

657
00:31:55.482 --> 00:31:56.618
That's probably him now.

658
00:32:01.021 --> 00:32:03.558
I'm in the subway system.

659
00:32:03.591 --> 00:32:04.925
You are good to go.

660
00:32:07.995 --> 00:32:09.898
Our leader's been released!

661
00:32:13.601 --> 00:32:17.104
Now you will all be free.

662
00:32:22.610 --> 00:32:24.579
Uhh!

663
00:32:48.969 --> 00:32:50.270
Whatever
you're gonna do.

664
00:32:50.304 --> 00:32:51.940
do it now.

665
00:32:51.972 --> 00:32:53.641
We have to shut
that bomb down.

666
00:32:54.576 --> 00:32:56.644
OK. I'm gonna disable
the pressure valve.

667
00:32:56.678 --> 00:32:57.745
Too late.

668
00:32:57.779 --> 00:32:58.979
Wait. no!

669
00:33:13.126 --> 00:33:14.829
Freeze! Police!

670
00:33:34.816 --> 00:33:37.017
What the hell was that?

671
00:33:38.485 --> 00:33:39.921
Excuse me?

672
00:33:39.954 --> 00:33:41.355
You know what
I'm talking about.

673
00:33:41.388 --> 00:33:43.323
You mean the part
where I saved our lives?

674
00:33:43.357 --> 00:33:45.727
No. the part where
you took a chance
with my life.

675
00:33:45.760 --> 00:33:48.061
Which you still have.
thanks to me.

676
00:33:48.095 --> 00:33:50.197
You cut the wire without
knowing what would happen.

677
00:33:50.230 --> 00:33:52.132
Because I knew what
would happen if I didn't.

678
00:33:52.165 --> 00:33:53.935
You do realize the only way
you win this argument

679
00:33:53.968 --> 00:33:55.335
is by being dead. right?

680
00:33:55.369 --> 00:33:56.871
No. because my way
would have worked.

681
00:33:56.905 --> 00:33:58.372
only you didn't give
me a chance because

682
00:33:58.405 --> 00:34:00.073
I didn't go to some
fancy private school.

683
00:34:00.107 --> 00:34:01.843
but that does not make you
smarter than me.

684
00:34:01.876 --> 00:34:03.243
I never said that.

685
00:34:03.277 --> 00:34:05.747
Yeah. You did when
you cut that wire.

686
00:34:07.047 --> 00:34:09.349
This isn't
your daddy's game show.

687
00:34:09.383 --> 00:34:11.151
Now. why don't you go
back to your cozy bedroom

688
00:34:11.184 --> 00:34:12.787
on the top floor
of your mansion.

689
00:34:14.121 --> 00:34:15.723
Easier to look down
on me from there.

690
00:34:21.428 --> 00:34:23.798
While
the hostage situation
has been resolved.

691
00:34:23.831 --> 00:34:27.301
the leader of the Mutant Gang
is once again at large.

692
00:34:27.334 --> 00:34:29.537
but Gotham can rest
a bit easier tonight.

693
00:34:29.571 --> 00:34:33.007
thanks in part to
the heroic efforts--and fists--

694
00:34:33.041 --> 00:34:35.342
of District Attorney
Harvey Dent.

695
00:34:38.278 --> 00:34:41.114
Mr. Dent. we didn't find
any explosive devices
on the premises.

696
00:34:41.148 --> 00:34:43.383
What? He had a detonator.

697
00:34:43.417 --> 00:34:46.888
We swept
the facility. including
the ventilator ducts.

698
00:34:46.921 --> 00:34:49.323
Nothing.
Maybe the Mutants
were bluffing

699
00:34:49.356 --> 00:34:50.625
to get their
leader out.

700
00:34:51.893 --> 00:34:53.093
Damn it.

701
00:34:54.294 --> 00:34:56.463
So. we save everyone's lives

702
00:34:56.496 --> 00:34:58.633
and Harvey Dent
gets all the credit?

703
00:34:59.567 --> 00:35:01.401
Look. he can have
the credit as long as

704
00:35:01.435 --> 00:35:03.170
we can have
the shiny stuff.

705
00:35:05.907 --> 00:35:07.875
And what
the Mutants take...

706
00:35:09.242 --> 00:35:11.111
we taketh away.

707
00:35:13.347 --> 00:35:16.183
I know what
you're gonna say.
"This is so wrong.

708
00:35:16.216 --> 00:35:18.418
The gala guests
were victims. too."

709
00:35:24.926 --> 00:35:26.326
Not all of them.

710
00:35:30.064 --> 00:35:31.298
It's a Court of Owls watch.

711
00:35:31.331 --> 00:35:32.800
Just like
the one Ford had.

712
00:35:37.005 --> 00:35:38.271
So is this one.

713
00:35:40.608 --> 00:35:41.909
The Court of Owls
were at the gala

714
00:35:41.943 --> 00:35:43.210
and we didn't even
know it.

715
00:35:43.243 --> 00:35:44.712
There were
over 200 people there.

716
00:35:44.746 --> 00:35:46.714
Which means we have no way
of knowing who they are.

717
00:35:46.748 --> 00:35:49.050
Well. maybe this
will help us find them.

718
00:35:49.083 --> 00:35:50.585
As promised.
Every scrap of paper

719
00:35:50.618 --> 00:35:52.386
the GCPD has on
Alan Wayne's death.

720
00:35:52.419 --> 00:35:54.756
Autopsy reports. eyewitness
statements. all of it.

721
00:35:54.789 --> 00:35:56.490
If the Court did kill him.
hopefully there's

722
00:35:56.524 --> 00:35:58.425
something in here
that'll lead us to them.

723
00:36:07.969 --> 00:36:09.202
Uhh!

724
00:36:11.304 --> 00:36:13.541
Think I'll do your
sparring partner a favor

725
00:36:13.574 --> 00:36:14.876
and call a TKO.

726
00:36:17.244 --> 00:36:18.445
They let him go.

727
00:36:19.413 --> 00:36:21.983
After everything
the Mutant Leader has done.

728
00:36:22.016 --> 00:36:23.350
and all the people
he's hurt.

729
00:36:25.153 --> 00:36:26.386
And they let him go.

730
00:36:27.387 --> 00:36:29.991
I know.
It's insane.

731
00:36:30.024 --> 00:36:31.258
It's Gotham.

732
00:36:33.528 --> 00:36:37.865
You try to change it
and it just changes you.

733
00:36:40.935 --> 00:36:42.603
Makes me wonder
why I even do it.

734
00:36:43.571 --> 00:36:45.205
Because you're
really good at it.

735
00:36:51.546 --> 00:36:54.882
Not easy to say it.
but I gotta admit:

736
00:36:57.051 --> 00:36:58.418
I'm jealous of you.

737
00:37:00.220 --> 00:37:02.355
I see why my dad
wanted you as his Robin.

738
00:37:05.325 --> 00:37:08.129
I just wish I'd gotten
to see that side of him.

739
00:37:08.162 --> 00:37:11.199
Turner...you got
to see the side of him

740
00:37:11.231 --> 00:37:13.167
that I never did.

741
00:37:13.201 --> 00:37:16.904
The man who takes his kid
on camping trips.

742
00:37:20.041 --> 00:37:21.241
Dad.

743
00:37:24.377 --> 00:37:26.714
I was so young
when my dad died.

744
00:37:30.218 --> 00:37:32.653
I never got to experience
that kind of stuff.

745
00:37:36.958 --> 00:37:39.660
So. I'm jealous of you.

746
00:37:41.361 --> 00:37:43.164
Well. it's clear
from his journals

747
00:37:43.197 --> 00:37:44.665
how much he cared
about you.

748
00:37:46.601 --> 00:37:49.469
It's also clear just
how responsible he felt

749
00:37:49.504 --> 00:37:51.304
for every bad thing
that every bad guy

750
00:37:51.338 --> 00:37:53.440
did in Gotham
that he didn't stop.

751
00:37:54.942 --> 00:37:56.878
It was eating him
up inside.

752
00:37:56.911 --> 00:37:58.946
And I can't imagine
he'd want that for you.

753
00:38:00.480 --> 00:38:02.817
My dad didn't want me
going down his path.

754
00:38:04.018 --> 00:38:05.753
And I may never
know why.

755
00:38:07.655 --> 00:38:11.458
But I do know...
following in his footsteps

756
00:38:11.491 --> 00:38:13.694
makes me feel
closer to him.

757
00:38:15.062 --> 00:38:17.598
He wouldn't want you
to bear the weight
of his legacy alone.

758
00:38:19.100 --> 00:38:20.433
Let me help you.

759
00:38:23.638 --> 00:38:26.040
Risking your freedom
to save all those people?

760
00:38:27.241 --> 00:38:29.644
It was very brave.
And. Turner.

761
00:38:29.677 --> 00:38:31.879
your dad would be
so proud of you.

762
00:38:33.247 --> 00:38:35.415
Is that a yes?
Come on.

763
00:38:35.448 --> 00:38:38.519
What did you say that night
you followed my dad?

764
00:38:38.553 --> 00:38:40.555
What convinced him
to let you help him?

765
00:38:40.588 --> 00:38:43.024
I didn't convince him.
Not that time.

766
00:38:44.158 --> 00:38:46.260
He said no.
And then
I followed him again

767
00:38:46.294 --> 00:38:48.395
and then I asked him again
and he said no.

768
00:38:48.428 --> 00:38:49.997
Actually. I got
a lot of nos.

769
00:38:51.532 --> 00:38:52.934
But I just
kept on asking.

770
00:38:56.537 --> 00:38:57.905
I guess I never gave up.

771
00:38:59.707 --> 00:39:02.375
Kinda sucks to be
the Mutant Leader then.

772
00:39:02.409 --> 00:39:03.945
With that
kind of persistence...

773
00:39:05.880 --> 00:39:07.380
he won't be free for long.

774
00:39:24.565 --> 00:39:26.934
Was not easy.
but I got it.

775
00:39:26.968 --> 00:39:29.537
Not sure why you wanted that
from evidence lockup.

776
00:39:29.570 --> 00:39:31.038
I thought you hated him.

777
00:39:31.072 --> 00:39:32.874
Oh. I do.

778
00:39:32.907 --> 00:39:35.076
This is just so I
don't forget how much.

779
00:39:40.181 --> 00:39:41.481
Cullen?

780
00:39:41.515 --> 00:39:43.017
No. I don't want
to hear it.

781
00:39:43.050 --> 00:39:44.952
You walked into a building
with a bomb in it.

782
00:39:44.986 --> 00:39:46.721
You're the last person
who gets to lecture me

783
00:39:46.754 --> 00:39:48.723
about doing
something dangerous.
I can handle myself.

784
00:39:48.756 --> 00:39:50.958
- I know that.
- Really?

785
00:39:50.992 --> 00:39:52.994
'Cause you've been
treating me like some
weak. scared. little kid.

786
00:39:56.664 --> 00:39:58.065
backed down from a fight.

787
00:39:59.200 --> 00:40:03.403
Not against Dad.
not against anybody.

788
00:40:04.372 --> 00:40:08.475
Cullen. you are
the bravest person I know.

789
00:40:12.479 --> 00:40:14.715
I learned that from my
pain-in-the-ass sister. so.

790
00:40:23.925 --> 00:40:26.260
I've been a citizen
of Gotham my whole life.

791
00:40:26.294 --> 00:40:30.264
I grew up in Cobble Hill.
just across the river.

792
00:40:30.298 --> 00:40:32.133
Ha ha!
That's right.

793
00:40:34.769 --> 00:40:40.775
For as long as I can remember.
unchecked crime and corruption

794
00:40:40.808 --> 00:40:44.946
have cast a dark shadow
over this city.

795
00:40:44.979 --> 00:40:48.683
And I think it's time
we remind those criminals

796
00:40:48.716 --> 00:40:51.686
that we are not helpless.

797
00:40:51.719 --> 00:40:56.424
We will no longer live
in the grip of fear.

798
00:40:56.456 --> 00:40:59.360
That we will fight
for a better Gotham.

799
00:40:59.393 --> 00:41:03.764
fight for a brighter tomorrow.

800
00:41:08.468 --> 00:41:10.604
Get us the hell out of here!

801
00:41:13.708 --> 00:41:17.778
And we will let a new dawn
of hope shine down

802
00:41:17.812 --> 00:41:20.648
on the streets of
this great city.

803
00:41:20.681 --> 00:41:22.383
That is what I want.

804
00:41:22.416 --> 00:41:25.252
No! No!

805
00:41:25.286 --> 00:41:28.990
No! Oh. no! No!

806
00:41:30.591 --> 00:41:34.295
And that is why
I am running

807
00:41:34.328 --> 00:41:36.530
for mayor of Gotham.

807
00:41:37.305 --> 00:42:37.396
